{{Quote|Seriously?|[[Axe Woves]], when [[Paz Vizsla]] draws out a vibro-knife|<ref name="Spies">{{TheMandalorian|Chapter 23: The Spies}}</ref>}}
A '''vibroknife''',<ref name="Life Debt">''[[Aftermath: Life Debt]]''</ref> also styled as '''vibro-knife''',<ref name="Smuggler's Run">''[[Smuggler's Run: A Han Solo & Chewbacca Adventure]]''</ref> was a type of [[knife]] featuring a small, [[Vibroblade|vibrating blade]] that hummed when activated.<ref name="Life Debt" /> Those vibrations occurred at a high-frequency and greatly improved on the blade's ability to slash at enemies or sever things.<ref name="MangaVol2">[[The Mandalorian: The Manga, Vol. 2|''The Mandalorian: The Manga'', Vol. 2]]</ref> It was capable of cutting through metal materials, including [[droid]]s and [[stuncuffs]].

After the [[Galactic Civil War]], the [[bounty hunter]] [[Mandalorian]] [[Din Djarin]] wielded a vibro-knife as a close range weapon on multiple occasions.<ref name="Mando">''[[Star Wars: The Mandalorian]]''</ref> [[Lieutenant]] [[Weel]] of the [[First Order]] [[First Order Security Bureau|Security Bureau]] used a vibro-knife to interrogate [[Suralinda Javos]], though she bested him and used the knife first to escape her bonds then rescue [[Poe Dameron]] from a [[squad]] of [[First Order stormtrooper|stormtroopers]].<ref name="Poe Dameron 7">[[Poe Dameron 7|''Poe Dameron'' 7]]</ref> [[Devi]] carried a vibro-knife while [[Scavenger|scavenging]] on [[Jakku]].<ref name="Before the Awakening">''[[Before the Awakening]]''</ref>

